The paper deals with the computation of Boolean functions and Hamming distances, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of probabilistic polynomials and algebraic techniques also suggests information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the application of the algorithm to various problems involving pairs and similarity measures suggests data mining (cs.DM) as another likely sub-category.
